Faction.name: {=ghilmanClanName}The Sable Riders
Faction.text: {=taom_sableriders}The Sable Riders are a feared mercenary brotherhood of Variags, hailing from the steppe lands of Khand. These warriors fight not for land, nor for honor, but for gold

Faction.name: {=LqTTchsa}The Sons of Castamir
Faction.text: {=taom_sonsofcastamir}The Sons of Castamir are the descendants of the rebels who once sought to claim the throne of Gondor in the name of Castamir the Usurper. Though their ancestors were exiled to Umbar, many now wander as mercenaries, hiring their blades to anyone willing to pay. They still harbor hatred for the line of Eärnur and dream of one day restoring Castamir’s rule, though for now, they fight wherever coin and opportunity take them.

Faction.name: {=7k9izAvC}Wildmen of Dunland
Faction.text: {=bsPd5zri}The Wildmen of Dunland are fierce and rugged warriors who live in the hills and forests near Rohan. They harbor an old grudge against the people of Rohan, whom they blame for taking their lands generations ago. Dunlendings are known for their guerilla tactics and surprise attacks, making them dangerous foes to any who underestimate them. Though often seen as savages, they fight for what they believe is rightfully theirs and will ally with those who share their hatred for Rohan.

Faction.name: {=UmVjzPI4}Wandering Company
Faction.text: {=tae3lhXh}The Wandering Company is a loose band of adventurers, warriors, and rogues who roam Middle-earth in search of glory and gold. They consist of men and elves who have grown tired of a sedentary life and have chosen the path of the sword. Though they are not tied to any kingdom, they are known to take contracts from those who can afford their services. The Company is known for their unpredictability and fighting skills, making them a valuable but risky ally.

Faction.name: {=NObV048p}The Sand Vultures
Faction.text: {=taom_sandvultures}The Sand Vultures are an infamous band of Haradrim warriors, known for their ruthless ambushes in the burning deserts of Haradwaith. Feared by merchants and soldiers alike, they move like ghosts across the dunes, striking swiftly before vanishing into the shifting sands. Though they owe no loyalty to any king, they have often fought for the Black Serpent of Harad, raiding the lands of Gondor and its allies whenever the opportunity arises.

Faction.name: {=nh4Y3LOc}The Moonfang Reavers
Faction.text: {=taom_moonfangreavers}The Moonfang Reavers are among the wildest of the Dunlending warbands, warriors who forsake armor for speed, painted in woad and draped in the pelts of the beasts they slay. They believe the spirit of the wolf guides them in battle, granting them unnatural ferocity. To face a Moonfang warrior is to face a man who knows no fear, for they fight with the frenzy of a beast cornered, tearing through their foes in bloody rampages.

Faction.name: {=as2TiAIJ}The Blackwood Outriders
Faction.text: {=taom_blackwoodoutriders}The Blackwood Outriders are a band of outcasts, hunters, and renegades who roam the edges of Mirkwood, preying upon travelers and unwelcome invaders alike. Though many were once men of Dale or Rhovanion, they have long since abandoned their former lives, living as outlaws beneath the dark boughs. Skilled archers and deadly skirmishers, they strike from the shadows, fading into the depths of the forest before vengeance can find them.

Faction.name: {=MVHawAEp}The Shadow Daggers
Faction.text: {=taom_shadowdaggers}The Shadow Daggers are an elusive network of spies, cutthroats, and assassins, rumored to have roots in the dark streets of Umbar. Hired blades of the Corsair lords, they specialize in eliminating enemies from the shadows, poisoning wells, and sowing discord before open war. Their services are expensive, but those who cross them rarely live long enough to regret it.

Faction.name: {=7WL1LWdf}The Greyfin Marauders
Faction.text: {=taom_greyfinmarauders}The Greyfin Marauders are a notorious band of river raiders who make their home along the Celduin (Running River). Outlaws and smugglers, they strike at isolated river settlements, looting supplies and vanishing downstream before retribution can follow. Though they often fight for the highest bidder, their true allegiance is to gold, wine, and the thrill of the chase.

Faction.name: {=mtZu1l2j}The Ashborn
Faction.text: {=taom_ashborn}The Ashborn are the last remnants of dark cults once devoted to Sauron. Though their dark master has fallen, they still whisper prayers to the shadows, seeking to reignite the fires of his dominion. Among their ranks are zealots, black-robed warriors, and fallen men who refuse to accept the Dark Lord’s defeat. Though their numbers dwindle, their hatred burns as fiercely as ever, and their blades remain sharp.

Faction.name: {=8ba4tpRU}The Desert Stalkers
Faction.text: {=taom_desertstalkers}The Desert Stalkers are a wandering brotherhood of Haradrim warriors, bound by no kingdom and loyal only to their own. Born of the shifting sands, they are expert trackers, ambushers, and raiders, striking with deadly precision. To the merchants of Gondor and Umbar alike, they are little more than brigands, but in the deep desert, they are spoken of with reverence and fear.

Faction.name: {=6BvGhzao}The Fireborn Riders
Faction.text: {=taom_firebornriders}The Fireborn Riders are warriors of Rhûn, men who have cast aside their tribal loyalties in search of wealth and war. Swift and deadly, they are masters of the bow and spear, their horsemen striking like the burning wind that sweeps the steppe. Though many still whisper prayers to the Dark Lord in secret, they now serve whoever offers them the richest spoils of war.

Faction.name: {=o7ud4X2X}The Shadowkin
Faction.text: {=taom_shadowkin}The Shadowkin are a reclusive and enigmatic group, dwelling in the deepest forests of Middle-earth. Composed of outcast elves, exiles from Rhovanion, and those who have abandoned civilization, they survive by hunting, raiding, and vanishing like ghosts. While they have no master, they sometimes lend their bows to those who respect the old ways and pay them in kind.

Faction.name: {=eC6qIOzz}Guardians of Tharbad
Faction.text: {=9qAWNBvA} The Guardians of Tharbad are a proud and resilient group of warriors sworn to protect the once-great city of Tharbad, a crucial crossroads between the northern and southern realms of Middle-earth. Though Tharbad has seen its share of decline and hardship, the Guardians remain steadfast in their mission, patrolling the surrounding lands and ensuring that travelers, merchants, and settlers can move freely without fear of bandits or hostile creatures. Clad in well-worn mail and wielding an assortment of weapons, the Guardians are as much a symbol of hope as they are of defense. Their loyalty to the ideals of order and safety make them natural allies to those who seek to rebuild and unify the region. Often underestimated due to their modest resources, the Guardians of Tharbad embody the strength of a people who refuse to let their home be forgotten, standing firm against the forces of chaos that threaten their way of life.
